12 Technical appendix — neutrino planar overlay

Construct a 2‑surface Σ defined by constant neutrino phase between events A and B.  Solve only the local GR correction near each end:

S_{AB}=\int_A^B\!\frac{ds_\nu}{E(s_\nu)}\; +\;\sum_i \Delta t_i\bigl(g_{\mu\nu}^{(i)}\bigr),\tag{1}

where the first term is evaluated on Σ (global chronometer) and each  is a small local correction derived from the spacetime metric.


---

Glossary

Alcubierre metric – a speculative curved‑spacetime solution permitting super‑luminal coordinate velocities without local v > c.

Index of refraction (neutrino) – departure from unity  in rock.

Signal Causality Constraint (SCC) – all carriers acquire relativistic distortion; communication therefore needs a normalisation layer.

General Relativity (GR) – Einstein's theory describing gravity as the curvature of spacetime caused by mass and energy.

Photon – a quantum of light; traditionally used as the causal reference in relativity.

Neutrino – a nearly massless, weakly interacting particle capable of traversing vast cosmic distances with minimal distortion.

Neutrino Oscillation – the quantum phenomenon by which neutrinos change 'flavor' (type) as they travel, sensitive to path length and energy; Muon, Electron, Tau Neutrinos.

Causal Triangulation – a geometric method using neutrino signals to create a stable frame of reference between points in spacetime concurrently proposed to use Law of Cosines to derive a stable 'C' reference from A and B.

Paraboloid Geometry – a shape representing local curvature in GR, relevant for understanding time dilation and geodesics.

Spacetime Distortion – the bending of spacetime due to gravity, which affects the propagation of signals and the measurement of time.

Time Dilation – the phenomenon where time appears to move slower in strong gravitational fields or at high velocities, per GR.

Geometric Intelligence – a conceptual framework that links intelligence propagation with stable geometric structures.

Causal Ethics – a philosophical model that applies causality and systemic awareness to guide ethical behavior.

Law of Cosines – a trigonometric law used here to determine a third reference point within a triangulated causal frame.

Planar Overlay – a 2D reference plane constructed between two points using neutrino behavior to bypass complex field calculations.

Phase Clock – the oscillatory phase of neutrinos, dependent on path and energy, used here as a distributed timing mechanism.

Causal Normalisation – a framework for reconstructing signal coherence between time-dilated reference frames.

Metric Perturbation – local deformation of the spacetime metric, used here as a small correction added to the baseline integral.

Null Geodesic – the path followed by light or massless particles through curved spacetime, defining the light-cone.

Shapiro Delay – time delay of a signal as it passes near a massive object due to spacetime curvature, often affecting photons.

Phase-Locked Beam – a neutrino stream emitted with fixed phase relations, useful for encoding coherent clock signals over distance.

